      "message": "Good point. Fixed in PS36.\n\nThe RX queue multi-buffer state is now initialized when queues are created, and reset/drained on admin state transitions via ``af_xdp_device_input_reset()`. This frees any partial multi-buffer chain, drains pending RX descriptors, and clears ``mb_head_bi`, ``mb_tail_bi`, and ``mb_total_len`` before the interface is brought back up/refilled.",
